教學方法 Teaching Strategies
      課堂講授，學生參與討論，測驗。    

		※請遵守智慧財產權觀念  不得不法影印
		 Please follow the Intellectual Property instruction and No illegal copy
	

課程教材 Course Material
	    Abstract Algebra, by Pierre Antoine Grillet (2007).
學校圖書館的網頁可以找到此書的電子版。    

參考書目 References


備註 Remarks
     以下是關於下學期(代數通論二)的課程簡介：

1. 我們延續上學期的用書。
2. 本學期介紹各類代數研究領域的基本概念，其中包括基本數論,交換/非交換代數,基本的群表現論,以及基本的同調代數。
3. 教學目標是讓學生瞭解整個大的脈絡，有時候會有一些細節交由學生課後自行學習。
4. 課程評分標準為：課堂參與40%+期末報告60%。
5. 期末報告為口頭及書面報告，由學生自行選定跟代數相關的主題。主要的內容是對於某個(或某些)問題的背景知識做一個整理然後對於這個問題做一個清楚的描述。這樣的報告可以視為一個微型的研究計劃，目的是讓有意願選擇代數方向來做論文的學生可以提早準備，因此建議學生可與指導老師討論可能的主題方向。




基本素養 Basic Literacy
        無    

核心能力 Competence
□ 掌握連續與逼進的能力
 Ability to handle continuity phenomena and approximations.
■ 處理數字及符號運算的能力
 Ability to operate with symbols and digits.
■ 透視形像與空間的能力
 Ability to visualize space, shape, and images.
□ 利用計算機處理數學的能力
 Ability of computer to do mathematics.
□ 應用隨機理論的能力
 Ability to apply stochastic mathematics.
□ 處理大量數據的能力
 Ability to handle large amount of data.
■ 處理離散型數學的能力
 Ability to do mathematics relating to discrete models.
□ 獨立研究與撰寫論文的能力
 Ability to do independent researches and to write thesis.
□ 使用計算機的能力
 Abilities to use computer as a tool.
 

課程概述 Course Description
       群同構定理，群作用，西羅定理，阿貝爾群基本定理，若爾當-赫爾德定理，p-群，冪零群，可解群。Basic concepts, the isomorphism theorems for groups, group actions, Sylow theorems, fundamental theorem of abelian groups, Jordan-Holder theorem, p-groups, nilpotent and solvable groups.    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    瞭解群環體的基本性質，最終的目標是理解如何用Galois理論解決古希臘尺規作圖的問題以及證明五次以上的多項式方程式沒有根式解。

課程綱要如下(每週約會完成2個lectures):
* : 不在測驗的範圍中

Lecture 1*:  Course outline/requirements/Motivation(theorem 8.7, corollary 9.7-9,9.11)
Lecture 2:  I.1-3: semigroups, groups, subgroups
Lecture 3:  I.4-5: homomorphisms, quotients, isomorphisms
Lecture 4:  I.6-7: free groups, presentations
Lecture 5:  II.1-2: direct products, direct sums, Krull-Schmidt theorem
Lecture 6:  II.3: group actions
Lecture 7:  II.4: symmetric groups
Lecture 8:  II.5: Sylow’s theorems
Lecture 9:  II.7: composition series, Jordan—Hölder’s theorem
Lecture 10*: II.8: general linear groups
Lecture 11*: II.9: solvable groups and nilpotent groups
MIDTERM EXAM 1
Lecture 12:  III.1-2: rings, subrings, ideals
Lecture 13:  III.3 quotients and homomorphisms
Lecture 14:  III.4 domains and fields
Lecture 15:  III.5-6 polynomial rings
Lecture 16:  III.7,9 formal power series/ rational functions
Lecture 17:  III.8 principal ideal domains
Lecture 18:  III.10 unique factorization domains
Lecture 19*:  III.11 Noetherian rings.
Lecture 20*:  III.12 Gröbner bases
Lecture 21:  IV.1-2 fields and field extensions
Lecture 22:  IV.3.4 algebraic extensions, algebraic closure
MIDTERM EXAM 2
Lecture 23: IV.5 separable extensions
Lecture 24: IV.6 purely inseparable extensions
Lecture 25*: IV.7 resultants and discriminants
Lecture 26: IV.8 transcendental extensions
Lecture 27: V.1 splitting fields
Lecture 28: V.2 normal extensions
Lecture 29: V.3 Galois extensions
Lecture 30: V.5 polynomial equations of degree 3 and 4
Lecture 31: V.6 cyclotomy
Lecture 32: V.7 norm and trace
Lecture 33*: V.8 solvability by radicals
Lecture 34*: V.9 geometric constructions
FINAL     

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Course outline/ basic definitions in group theory2morphisms and quotients/ free groups and presentations3Krull-Schmidt theorem/ group actions4symmetric groups/ Sylow's theorems5Jordan—Holder’s theorem/general linear groups6solvable groups/ nilpotent groups71ST MIDTERM EXAM/ basic definition in ring theory/ quotients and morphisms 8domains, fields, polynomial rings9principal ideal domains, unique factorization domains10Noetherian rings/ Grobner bases11fields, field extensions, algebraic closure122ND MIDTERM EXAM/separable and purely inseparable extensions13resultants and discriminants/ transcendental extensions14splitting fields and normal extensions15Galois extensions/ polynomial equations of degree 3 and 416cyclotomy/ norm and trace17solvability by radicals/ geometric constructions18FINAL EXAM 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


